#Text=Wikinews interviews Spanish Paralympic swimmer Marta Gómez
#Text=Wikinews interviews Marta Gomez .
#Text=Image : Laura Hale .
#Text=Marta Gomez at Madrid – Barajas Airport yesterday
#Text=Image : Laura Hale .
#Text=Sunday , August 11 , 2013

#Text=Thursday at Madrid – Barajas Airport , Wikinews interviewed Spanish Paralympic swimmer Marta Gomez , who is scheduled to compete at the 2013 IPC Swimming World Championships that start on Monday in Montreal , Canada .
#Text=This is Laura Hale , I 'm interviewing Marta Gómez , a Spanish Paralympic swimmer going to the 2013 IPC Swimming World Championships in Montreal .
#Text=Are you going to Montreal and what strokes and distances are you competing in ?
#Text=Marta Gomez : I 'll swim the 100 meter and 400 freestyle , and the 200 individual medley .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Voy a nadar los 100 [ metros ] y 400 libres , y los 200 estilo giro .
#Text=Have you won any medals at previous championships ?
#Text=Spanish language : ‍¿Vas a ganar alguna medalla ?
#Text=In 2011 , at the European Championships in Berlin , I won 3 bronze .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍En Europeo 2011 , en Berlín , gané 3 bronces .
#Text=Do you think you will win any medals in Montreal ?
#Text=Spanish language : ‍¿Tienes medalla en Montreal ?
#Text=I will try to fight for a medal in the 400 freestyle which is my main event , but , well , [ if I swim well and feel well ] my options are clearer , but until you swim nothing is clear .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Voy a intentar luchar por la medalla en el 400 libres que es mi prueba principal , pero bueno , hay que ¿ sentir ?
#Text=y nadarlos ; la ¿ ?
#Text=serán mis opciones más claras , pero hasta que no se nade no hay nada claro .
#Text=You 've competed at previous Paralympic Games ?
#Text=In London ?
#Text=Yes .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Sí .
#Text=And you did n't win any medals ?
#Text=No , I did n't win any medals .
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍No .
#Text=Fui de cima en Londres .
#Text=What 's the difference
#Text=preparing for London to the World Championships ?
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍¿Cuál es la diferencia de la preparación para Londres para el Campeonato del Mundo ?

#Text=That I have improved many aspects of technical level [ like ? ] performance , and especially the psychological aspect that after London I have faced other competitions and I feel much more confident about myself and I have become more competitive .

#Text=Spanish language : ‍Que yo he mejorado muchos aspectos tanto a nivel de técnica como de rendimiento , y sobre todo el aspecto psicológico que a raíz de Londres he afrontado las competiciones de otra manera y me siento mucho más segura de mí misma y me he vuelto más competitiva .
#Text=Are you a swimmer with a visual impediment ?
#Text=You cannot see ... ?
#Text=Spanish language : ‍-¿De qué categoría eres ?
#Text=S13 .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍S13 .
#Text=When you swim , can you see the swimmers next to you ?
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍¿Cuando nadas , se puede ver a los nadadores a tu lado ?

#Text=Depending on the race , you will always be able to — some races like in short distances like the 100 meter breaststroke and 100 meter freestyle as it is too short to lose sight of your rivals , but for example in 400 meters , yes , but I can only see from the sides .
#Text=I cannot see all the swimmers .
#Text=In the 800 meters , seeing swimmers in the race is impossible : I fail to see them .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Depende de la prueba , siempre va ...

#Text=la de velocidad en pruebas cortas ... por ejemplo en 100 [ metros ] brazas y 100 libres al ser tan cortas no vas tan pendiente de los rivales , pero por ejemplo en 400 sí que puedo ver más pero solamente a las que tengo a los lados , no puedo ver a todas las nadadoras , a las 8 nadadoras de la serie es imposible , no alcanzo a verlas .
#Text=When you swim , do you mostly think about your own race because you cannot fully see everyone ?
#Text=Do you race more against yourself because you can not see ?
#Text=Spanish language : ‍¿Nadas más contigo misma o por no poder ver ?
#Text=¿ más tu prueba ?
#Text=Yes , of course .
#Text=Not being able to see your rivals you have to concentrate on your event because you may have nobody to [ watch ? ] , you may have a slight reference but you have to swim against yourself .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Sí , claro .
#Text=Al no poder ver a las rivales te tienes que ¿ dedicar ?
#Text=a hacer tu prueba porque no tienes a lo mejor a nadie en quién fijarte , puedes tener una ligera referencia pero tienes que nadar tu prueba y nadar contigo misma .
#Text=Why did you choose swimming as opposed to athletics or Goalball or some other sport ?

#Text=I have only practiced swimming since childhood , I 've always liked the water and it 's been the only sport I 've practiced because I think it 's a sport where you feel a lot of freedom and do n't have any architectural barriers or anything .

#Text=Spanish language : ‍Yo solo he practicado la natación desde pequeña , siempre me ha gustado mucho el agua y ha sido el único deporte que he practicado porque me parece un deporte en que sientes mucha libertad y no tienes ningún tipo de barreras arquitectónicas ni nada .
#Text=Gracías .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Thank you .
#Text=De nada .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍You 're welcome .
